ball.annotation.processing

  • Packages that use ball.annotation.processing 
    Package Description
    ball.annotation
    Provides Annotation implementation classes.
    ball.annotation.processing
    Provides Processor implementation classes.
    ball.http.annotation
    Provides Annotation implementation classes.
    ball.http.annotation.processing
    Provides Processor implementation classes.
    ball.tools.javac
    Provides javac plug-ins.
    ball.upnp.annotation

    ball.upnp.annotation.processing
    Provides Processor implementation classes.
    ball.util.ant.taskdefs
    See org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.
  • Classes in ball.annotation.processing used by ball.annotation 
    Class and Description
    AnnotationValueMustConvertTo
    Annotation to test an Annotation can be converted to a specified Class.
  • Classes in ball.annotation.processing used by ball.annotation.processing 
    Class and Description
    AbstractProcessor
    Provides abstract base class for Processor by providing a AbstractProcessor.getSupportedSourceVersion() implementation, methods to report Diagnostic.Kind.ERRORs and Diagnostic.Kind.WARNINGs, and access to ProcessingEnvironment.getFiler(), ProcessingEnvironment.getElementUtils(), and ProcessingEnvironment.getTypeUtils().
    AnnotatedNoAnnotationProcessor
    Abstract Processor base class for processing "no" Annotation ("*").
    AnnotatedProcessor
    Abstract Processor base class for processing Annotations specified by @For.
    ClassFileProcessor
    Interface to provide an alternate entry point for annotation processing on compiled class files.
    For
    AnnotatedProcessor Annotation to specify Annotations.
    ForElementKinds
    AnnotatedNoAnnotationProcessor Annotation to specify ElementKind criteria.
    ForSubclassesOf
    AnnotatedNoAnnotationProcessor Annotation to specify super-Class criteria.
    JavaxLangModelUtilities
    Utility methods for Processor and Taglet implementations.
    MustImplement
    Annotation to specify required super-Class criteria a Class must implement.
    TargetMustExtend
    Annotation to specify required super-Class criteria an annotated Class must extend.
    WithoutModifiers
    AnnotatedNoAnnotationProcessor Annotation to specify Modifiers that should be absent from the target.
